      "text": "STATE OF NEW YORK PUBLIC SERVICE COMMISSION At a session of the Public Service Commission held in the City of New York on November 16, 2023\n\nCOMMISSIONERS PRESENT: \nRory M. Christian, Chair \nDiane X. Burman \nJames S. Alesi \nJohn B. Howard \nDavid J. Valesky \nJohn B. Maggiore \nCASE 22-E-0064 – Proceeding on Motion of the Commission as to \nthe Rates, Charges, Rules and Regulations of \nConsolidated Edison Company of New York, Inc. \nfor Electric Service. \nCASE 22-G-0065 – Proceeding on Motion of the Commission as to \nthe Rates, Charges, Rules and Regulations of \nConsolidated Edison Company of New York, Inc. \nfor Gas Service. \nORDER APPROVING TARIFF AMENDMENTS ON A PERMANENT BASIS \n(Issued and Effective November 20, 2023) \nBY THE COMMISSION: \nINTRODUCTION \nOn July 27, 2023, Consolidated Edison Company of \nNew York, Inc. (Con Edison or the Company) filed amendments to \nits electric and gas tariff schedules and statements, P.S.C. No. \n10 – Electricity, P.S.C. No. 12 – Electricity and P.S.C. No. 9 – \nGas, as required by the Commission’s 2023 Rate Order issued in \n\n-2-\n\nthese proceedings.1 These amendments became effective on a temporary basis on August 1, 2023. On August 25, 2023, Con Edison filed further revisions to its tariff schedules, P.S.C. No. 10 – Electricity and P.S.C. No. 12 – Electricity, which became effective on a temporary basis on September 1, 2023. The amendments filed on July 27, 2023, and on August 25, 2023, effectuate the rates and provisions for Rate Year (RY) 1, the twelve-month period from January 1, 2023, to December 31, 2023. By this Order, the Commission authorizes the tariff amendments and statements listed in the Appendix to become effective on a permanent basis as of the date of issuance of this Order.\n\nBACKGROUND \nThe 2023 Rate Order adopted the terms of the Joint \nProposal establishing a three-year rate plan for electric and \ngas service for the period beginning January 1, 2023, through \nDecember 31, 2025.2 The approved rate plan provides for a RY 1 \nincrease to electric delivery revenues of approximately \n$457.5 million, or 6.6 percent, and a RY 1 increase in gas \ndelivery revenues of $187 million, or 10.7 percent. \nImplementation of the 2023 Rate Order required \nnumerous amendments to Con Edison’s electric and gas tariffs and \nstatements. The 2023 Rate Order directed Con Edison to file, on \nnot less than five days’ notice, electric and gas tariff \n1 Cases 22-E-0064 and 22-G-0065, Con Edison – Electric and Gas \nRates, Order Adopting Terms of Joint Proposal and Establishing \nElectric and Gas Rate Plans with Additional Requirements \n(issued July 20, 2023) (2023 Rate Order). \n2 The second rate year (RY 2) of the 2023 Rate Order is the \ntwelve-month period beginning January 1, 2024, and ending \nDecember 31, 2024. The third rate year (RY 3) is the twelve \nmonth period beginning January 1, 2025, and ending \nDecember 31, 2025. \n\n-3-\n\namendments, as necessary, to effectuate the RY 1 terms to become \neffective on August 1, 2023, on a temporary basis. Any comments \non the compliance filing were to be filed within 10 days of \nservice of the Company’s proposed amendments. The amendments \nset forth in the compliance filing would not become effective on \na permanent basis until approved by the Commission and are \nsubject to refund if any showing is made that the amendments are \nnot in compliance with the 2023 Rate Order. \nTARIFF FILINGS \nOn July 27, 2023, Con Edison filed amendments to its \nelectric and gas tariff schedules and statements to implement \nthe RY 1 terms as required in the 2023 Rate Order. On \nAugust 25, 2023, Con Edison filed further revisions to P.S.C. \nNo. 10 – Electricity and P.S.C. No. 12 – Electricity, adding \nclarifying language to the Value Stack sections of the tariffs, \nas approved by the 2023 Rate Order. The August 25, 2023 \nrevisions specify that customers receiving Value Stack credits \nmore than two months after the Value Stack generators’ \napplicable bill period ends, will be credited $10 for each month \nbeyond two months that the Value Stack credits are delayed. \nThese credits are retroactive to June 1, 2023, will be on \ncustomer accounts when Value Stack credits are provided, will \nnot be provided when the credit delay is caused by Con Edison \nnot receiving an up-to-date subscriber list and/or allocations, \nand will end if the Commission adopts a statewide negative \nrevenue adjustment and/or customer compensation requirement for \nbilling and crediting these customers. \nCon Edison complied with the requirements of newspaper \npublication pursuant to Public Service Law (PSL) §66(12)(b) and \nTitle 16 of the New York Codes, Rules and Regulations §720-8.1 \nfor its filing made on July 27, 2023. Con Edison requested a \n\n-4-\n\nwaiver of the newspaper requirement for the further revisions \nfiled on August 25, 2023, as the revisions were previously \npublished. The Appendix to this Order sets forth a list of the \ntariff amendments and statements filed by the Company and the \ndates of newspaper publication. No comments were filed in \nresponse to Con Edison’s compliance filings. \nLEGAL AUTHORITY \nPursuant to PSL §§5, 65(1), and 66(1) and (12), the \nCommission has the legal authority to review the proposed tariff \nleaves, as well as modify, reject or approve such filed tariffs \nto ensure that the rates and services governed by those tariffs \nare just and reasonable and otherwise consistent with law. As \nsuch, the Commission has the legal authority to review, approve, \nand make effective the Company’s filed tariff amendments, as \nprescribed in this Order. \nDISCUSSION AND CONCLUSION \nCon Edison’s proposed tariff amendments and statements \nproperly reflect the requirements of the 2023 Rate Order, \nincluding the rates, charges, and terms necessary to effectuate \nRY 1, with a housekeeping modification discussed below. In \naddition, no comments on the Company’s proposed amendments have \nbeen received. Accordingly, the Commission authorizes the \ntariff amendments and statements listed in the Appendix to \nbecome effective on a permanent basis as of the date of issuance \nof this Order, with the exception of the tariff amendments \ndiscussed below. \nThe following tariff amendments will remain in effect \non a temporary basis until the changes are acted upon by the \nCommission in the respective proceedings: (1) amendments to \nleaves 3, 329, 352, and 359.1 in P.S.C. No. 10 – Electricity \n\n-5-\n\nthat were filed in Case 18-E-0138; (2) amendments to leaves 162, \n253.9, and 384 in P.S.C. No. 10 – Electricity that were filed in \nCase 19-E-0079; and (3) amendments to leaf 3 in P.S.C. No. 10 – \nElectricity, and leaves 77.2 and 79 in P.S.C. No. 9 – Gas that \nwere filed in Case 22-M-0159.3 For leaf 387 of P.S.C. No. 10 – \nElectricity, the Company inadvertently deleted “SERVICE \nCLASSIFICATION NO. 1” from the title section of this leaf. To \nmake it clear that the information on leaf 387 is for Service \nClassification No. 1, the Company shall file within ten days of \nthe issuance of this Order, a further revision to leaf 387 to \nreinsert the deleted text. \nThe Commission approves the request for the waiver of \nnewspaper publication for the tariff amendments filed on \nAugust 25, 2023, as the revisions add language approved in the \n2023 Rate Order and the Company provided newspaper publication \nfor the changes approved in the 2023 Rate Order for RY 1. The \nCommission also waives the requirement for newspaper publication \nfor the further revision directed in this Order to leaf 387 of \nP.S.C. No. 10 – Electricity as this change is housekeeping in \nnature. \nThe Commission orders: \n1. The tariff amendments and statements filed by \nConsolidated Edison Company of New York, Inc., and listed in the \n3 Case 18-E-0138, Proceeding on Motion of the Commission \nRegarding Electric Vehicle Supply Equipment and \nInfrastructure, Order Approving Managed Charging Programs with \nModifications (issued July 14, 2022); Case 19-E-0079, In the \nMatter of the Continuation of Stand",
